// Module: Diet and Recipes (Human and Pet): Recipes Map Nearby healthy restaurants Preparation Ingredients Steps to follow Pet Diet Pet Suitable for: %1$s Diet Description Make sure to consult with your veterinarian for the ideal portions according to your pet\'s weight and breed!
// Human Recipe 1: Chicken: Chicken with Rice and Vegetables A balanced dish, high in protein and easy to digest to maintain your pet\'s energy.
150g cooked and shredded chicken breast (no salt)
50g cooked brown rice
30g grated carrot
20g finely diced zucchini
Cook the chicken breast in boiling water without adding salt, garlic, or onion.
In another pot, steam the brown rice and vegetables until soft.
Shred the chicken perfectly once cold to prevent choking.
Mix the chicken, rice, and vegetables in a bowl and let cool to room temperature before serving.
// Human Recipe 2: Salmon: Salmon with Sweet Potato and Peas Excellent source of Omega-3 for a shiny coat and cardiovascular health.
120g cooked salmon fillet
1 medium boiled sweet potato
a pinch of steamed peas
Boil the sweet potato until soft and cut into cubes.
Steam or grill the salmon (without oil).
Meticulously remove all bones from the fish.
Mix everything in your pet\'s bowl.
// Pet Recipes Database: Homemade Chicken Kibble A balanced and delicious recipe to spoil your furry friend. 250 kcal Dog Refreshing Strawberry Ice Treats Frozen treats perfect for hot summer days. They help to cool down. 80 kcal Dog / Cat Oatmeal and Banana Cookies Crunchy baked treats, easy to break into small pieces. 120 kcal Dog Magic Bone Broth Ideal for keeping joints hydrated and improving digestion. 95 kcal Dog / Cat
// Module: Physical Activity and Challenges: View nearby parks DURATION INTENSITY Routine Detail Duration: Intensity: Exercise Instructions Interactive Challenge Module Do the activity with your pet now! Cancel Training Challenge Completed! You have earned +%1$d Happiness Points. The record was successfully saved in your walk log. Play Again Press start to time your real session and earn points. Start Real Challenge Remember to bring enough water for you and your pet during the training! Physical play session successfully completed! Earned
// Physical Activities List: Light Canicross Continuous jogging where your dog is attached to your waist with an elastic harness. Ideal for improving cardiovascular endurance for both. Homemade Agility Create an obstacle course with cones and low hurdles. Combine squats (you) with jump and speed commands (your pet). Interval Walk Alternate 2 minutes of fast walking with 1 minute of explosive jogging. Strengthens your dog\'s joints and burns calories. Fetch and Deploy Throw their favorite toy. While your dog runs to fetch it, do as many lunges or push-ups as you can until they return. Doga (Dog Yoga) Stretching Guided deep body stretching session where you involve your pet by maintaining balance postures together. Frisbee Cardio Trail Sprint in zigzag catching flying discs. Develops extreme agility, reflexes, and explosive acceleration in open spaces.
// Duration / Intensity Labels: 15 min 20 min 25 min 30 min 40 min Low Medium High Low - Medium
