// Module: Health and Vaccines: Health and Vaccines Vaccines Treatments History Add record Find Vets Essential Vaccination Guide Make sure to keep your pet\'s vaccination schedule up to date. Rabies Vaccine 🦠 Mandatory by law. Applied for the first time at 3-4 months of age and requires a mandatory annual booster. 5-in-1 / Feline Triple Vaccine 🐕🐈 Protects against deadly diseases like Parvovirus, Distemper, Hepatitis, and Leptospirosis. Annual booster. Giardiasis Vaccine 🧼 Optional but highly recommended if your pet frequently visits public parks or interacts with other animals. Parasite Control and Medication Key information for daily preventive health. Internal Deworming 💊 Ideally performed every 3 to 4 months using the exact dose based on your pet\'s current weight. Flea and Tick Control 🛡️ Via monthly pipettes, collars, or chewable pills. Vital to prevent the transmission of diseases. Responsible Use of Medication ⚠️ Never self-medicate your pet. Incorrect dosages can severely damage their internal organs. New Health Record Vaccine Dewormer Note Name (e.g., Feline Triple, Flea Control) Date (DD/MM/YYYY) Additional notes or observations Save to Logbook No vaccines or notes recorded yet.\nUse the \'+\' button to add one.
// Module: Sleep (Human and Pet): Sleep Mode Sleep status Ready to rest! Recording sleep hours for you and your pet... Press the button when going to sleep. Wake Up Start Resting Your recent nights Pet Tips Your Pet\'s Rest Good morning!\nHow did you rest today? Select the emoji that best represents your energy and your pet\'s this morning. %1$s hrs
Adult dogs sleep between 12 and 14 hours a day. Make sure their space is comfortable!
Restless sleep in your pet may indicate they need more physical activity during the day.
Puppies can sleep up to 18 hours a day to support their rapid bone growth.
Avoid letting your pet sleep in direct drafts or very cold air conditioning.
